<p>

<b><it>Killshot</it></b> is a <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../825/35825.xml">
2008</link> <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../274/237274.xml">
thriller</link> film based on the 1989 novel <it><literary_composition wordnetid="106364329" confidence="0.8">
<written_communication wordnetid="106349220" confidence="0.8">
<writing wordnetid="106362953" confidence="0.8">
<fiction wordnetid="106367107" confidence="0.8">
<novel wordnetid="106367879" confidence="0.8">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../825/2291825.xml">
Killshot</link></novel>
</fiction>
</writing>
</written_communication>
</literary_composition>
</it> by <screenwriter wordnetid="110564400" confidence="0.9173553029164789">
<writer wordnetid="110794014" confidence="0.9173553029164789">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../908/412908.xml">
Elmore Leonard</link></writer>
</screenwriter>
.  The film is directed by <actor wordnetid="109765278" confidence="0.9508927676800064">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../312/351312.xml">
John Madden</link></actor>
 and stars <actor wordnetid="109765278" confidence="0.9173553029164789">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../355/306355.xml">
Diane Lane</link></actor>
 and <actor wordnetid="109765278" confidence="0.9508927676800064">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../511/1035511.xml">
Thomas Jane</link></actor>
 as a couple who, despite being in a witness protection program, are discovered by the criminal they outed, portrayed by <actor wordnetid="109765278" confidence="0.9508927676800064">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../936/530936.xml">
Mickey Rourke</link></actor>
.</p>

